item.title: Understanding Graph Attention Networks (GAT)
item.description: Understanding Graph Attention Networks (GAT) -- This is 4th in the series of blogs Explained: Graph Representation Learning. Let’s dive right in, assuming you have read the first three. GAT (Graph Attention Network), is a novel neural network architectures that operate on graph-structured data, leveraging masked self-attentional layers to address the shortcomings of prior methods based on graph convolutions or their approximations.
